title: Theo Wisseh & Noah Young MSK Speaks On TikTok Boycott, Scam Rap, Groupies & More
description:
Great convo with Flakko and his lit guests Theo Wisseh and Noah MSK, where they talk about building their brands, being consistent, believing in your vision, fans, Collab Crib, and more!

-----
00:00 Intro
1:50 Their mutual friend brought up Theo's mom, Flakko and Theo could possibly be related
6:15 Theo started making content in 7th grade, Vine, etc, then met Noah and started working together
10:25 Theo and Noah really heavily connected during Covid they were close by so they linked up to go up together
11:31 Theo has been building his TikTok since 2018, and went viral 2 years ago when he graduated
13:23 Going to school knowing that you make more money than your teacher
14:55 Theo calls out Tiktok for picking and choosing who and what kinda content they push
16:20 Noah's curly hair video took off outta nowhere, 6M views, use your progress as motivation
17:22 Theo's dad jokes skit and sound
20:48 All his previous content partners didn't believe in the vision so they all left
22:38 Noah talks about Black creators being put in the back burner by social platforms
24:05 Keith gets on camera to talk about how he essentially reached out to creators to build the content house
27:33 Using social media as stepping stones to do acting and things like that
37:22 Noah says getting with girls who want you for clout is pointless
38:50 Noah has a girlfriend, but Theo would be open to an industry relationship
43:12 Theo says Kanye can't be programmed at this point anymore and that's a goal of his
44:57 Noah kinda fanned out over Deshae Frost coz he saw his growth
46:08 Theo wants to meet Jordan Peel and says he's highly inspired by his career path
46:35 There's no stopping Theo, he aspires to be a director, actor, everything
47:00 Created a crazy mosh pit at Rolling Loud last year, however, Theo would NEVER go to a Travis Scott concert
48:27 Noah has music dropping soon, weighs in on people not taking him seriously
50:31 You gotta be strategic, work hard, be consistent and have a little luck to be an influencer
